        <abstract>
            <p>Did not know about separation between Silurian and Cambrian.</p>
            <p>Cannot attend Geological Society meeting.</p>
            <p>Etty [Henrietta Darwin] ill.</p>
            <p>Sedgwick in his attack at Cambridge Philosophical Society states "there must be [on CD’s theory] large genera not varying".</p>
            <p>Discusses migration of plants and animals from Old World to New.</p> 
<p>Views of Asa Gray on <hi rend="italic">Aster</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Mentions flora of coal period.</p>
            <p>Has been elected to Philadelphia Academy of Natural Sciences.</p>
        </abstract>
